     		       Poseidon's Temple

printed name: "Poseidon's Temple"

description: "You see a coloumn with 4 rotatable discs. The discs have 5 faces, 4 of them with a picture and one empty. The pictures are the same on each disc and they are in order: Budding olives and fresh green leaves, Green olives growing in size, with fuller leaves, Ripe, darkening olives ready for harvest, some fallen to the ground and Bare branches with a few remaining leaves, the tree in a state of dormancy. The faces towards the altar are all empty."

Only then shall the twins unveil the hidden path.[otherwise]The inscription engraved on the gnomon read: At midday, let Apollo's light cast no shadow, and at midnight, let Artemis[apostrophe] glow guide the way.
